alert.note: Alert for Burnett (Wisconsin) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 15 at 1:55PM CDT until further notice by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 345 PM CDT MONDAY... * WHAT...Flooding caused by rain and snowmelt continues. * WHERE...A portion of northwest Wisconsin, including the following area, Burnett. * WHEN...Until 345 PM CDT Monday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 155 PM CDT, gauge and public reports high water on area rivers and streams. Flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the warned area. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Grantsburg, Siren, Webster, Falun, Alpha, Phantom Lake, Saint Croix State Park and Chengwatana State Forest. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
